This paper deals with the problem of wireless M2M communication, which is a subfield of computer networking. The proposed protocol involves random access and admission control, which are common topics in the subfield of network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with delay constraints, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The protocol also involves control and stability, which are topics in control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also deals with collision estimation, which is a topic in cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with M2M communication, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.MM (Machine Learning) a possible category.
